    LifeExpectancyParser

    parses the CSV format files of World bank data site that makes statistics about Life expectancy from 1960 to 2017 inclusive Should be instansiated using DataParserBuilder class only

    • Method Detail

      • parse

        public LifeExpectancyParser parse()
        Parses CSVFile and should be first method to get called. using the Apache csv parser and Apache CSV format classes uses the first record in the file as header and makes internally a map containing each record due to its index and its String column name using the default charset and default format of CSV uses the InputStream made by the AbstractDataParser and is accessed using the .getSource() method as it's private and uses the .addPojo(T pojo) to add the pojo object made from each record and it uses the entries List made by AbstractDataParser and it's of type LifeExpectancyEntry as you extended the AbstractCSV with LifeExpectancyEntry type parameter also that's why addPojo accepts LifeExpectancyEntry
        Returns:
        Same LifeExpectancyParser object used for API Flexibility to use Aggregate Operations, null if an un-handled exception happens
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if a null element was parsed
